listing.name: Citycenter, room+ensuite Canalhouse
listing.address: Houtkopersburgwal, Amsterdam, North Holland 1011 LL, Netherlands
listing.access: Guests have acces to their own private room and the ensuite bathroom. You can reach the room with the elevator. You have free Nespresso coffee and tea and also a refrigerator with free boiled water. You can reach your room with the elevator or the stairs.
listing.description:
Located just a 10-minute walk away from the buzzing Dam Square is this sleek room with en suite and a private entrance.  Guests have use of a coffeemaker, watercooker, refrigerator, flat-screen TV with a DVD player and free Wi-Fi (200 MB speed)




You are staying in a Canalhouse from 1612 under the roof. It is totally renovated of course.
It is a residents building, so it is a very quiet place to stay in the middle of the Citycenter.
From here you can walk to almost every place of interest in town.

Guests have acces to their own private room and the ensuite bathroom. You can reach the room with the elevator. You have free Nespresso coffee and tea and also a refrigerator with free boiled water. You can reach your room with the elevator or the stairs.

We meet each other at the check in and the check out. I check your room every day for things you probably need. If you have any questions, you can ring my bell. I am living next door.

The old centre of Amsterdam with the Canals is an open air Museum. It is beautiful to live there or to stay there. You can easy walk to the Red Light district or to the Waterloosquare market.
You can view the canalboats in front of the house.

Tramstop 9 and 14 are 200 meter away. Also Metrostop Nieuwmarkt or Waterlooplein are a 5 minutes walk away.

You can have breakfast around the corner or you can buy food at the large Albert Heijn supermarket around the corner.
listing.house_rules:
No Smoking in the whole building.
No drugs!
We do not accept checkins between 10 pm and 9 am.
When you check in on a Saturday, it is only possible to check in between 1 pm and 6 pm, not later.
listing.instant_book_welcome_message: Check in is possible between 2 pm and 10 pm. Please let me know your time of arrival at the airport or trainstation also when you are travelling by car to be sure that I am available upon your arrival

review.comments: This place is just perfect! Super neat and tidy, almost like it is professionally maintained. Private bathroom was nicely maintained and clean. Loved the fact that it was in a Canal house that was built way back in 1612. The location is super, 15 mins walk to Amsterdam Central. The canals are right outside and you can have a lovely stroll besides them. Gerard was super as a host! Communication was perfect and he even let us check-in a bit early. There were clear instructions in the room. Although we didn't quite get to meet him, the overall experience was fantastic!
